<subSubSection id="C331F4EFFFCF1D555053F9F1FF54F8CC" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B94A764FFCF1D555053F9F1FCD6F94C" blockId="17.[94,719,1562,1875]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFCF1D555053F9F1FC1AF9AC" bold="true" box="[94,359,1562,1587]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Differential diagnosis:</emphasis>
Head black; pronotum pale yellow, elytra black with apical yellow patches; males: fore femur swollen, with a distinct acute ventral tooth on distal third; aedeagus with right prolongation of tegmen broadly projected dorsally; left setiferous prolongation short; right paramere present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B94A764FFCF1D555089F931FF54F8CC" blockId="17.[94,719,1562,1875]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName id="4C2BDCE7FFCF1D555089F931FCA5F96C" authorityName="Brancucci" authorityYear="1981" box="[132,472,1754,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Macromalthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santaremensis">
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFCF1D555089F931FCA5F96C" box="[132,472,1754,1779]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Macromalthinus santaremensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BDCE7FFCF1D555263F931FDD4F88C" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1919" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Macromalthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maximiceps">
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFCF1D555263F931FDD4F88C" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. maximiceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2BDCE7FFCF1D5550D0F911FC0CF88C" authorityName="Brancucci" authorityYear="1981" box="[221,369,1786,1811]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Macromalthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belemensis">
<emphasis id="B95F7B76FFCF1D5550D0F911FC0CF88C" box="[221,369,1786,1811]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M.belemensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of right paramere. It differs from the other Amazonian species by truncate ventral tooth on fore femur of males.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
